{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778433164261,"sessionID":"ses_1ed2e2000ffeBIeUXmv2C8ceG7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_yDrqJ1IHNEDFdFB48o9evdya","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Added the missing term tracker link for `GO:0046923` so that all signal-sequence receptor updates from #31419 carry the issue provenance consistently.\n+\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added the missing `term_tracker_item` metadata to `GO:0046923` (`ER lumen protein retrieval receptor activity`) linking it to geneontology/go-ontology#31419.\n+\n+The imported PR diff already showed the intended label, definition, synonym, and parent updates in the local ontology. This follow-up makes the metadata consistent with the other edited signal-sequence receptor terms, which already carried the #31419 tracker link.\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+Ran `make travis_build` from `src/ontology` before and after the edit. Both runs passed all reported ROBOT/SPARQL validation checks.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: Issue context and imported PR diff reviewed.\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before changes.\n+- [x] RESEARCH: N/A; no new biological claims or references were introduced.\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Affected signal-sequence receptor terms were checked in `go-edit.obo`.\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Consulted the binding pattern and existing ontology precedent; no logical definition changes were needed.\n+- [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl` for `GO:0046923`.\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: N/A; no relationship changes were made.\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: N/A; no obsoletion, chemical entity, reaction, mapping, or taxon constraint changes were made.\n+- [x] METADATA: Added missing `term_tracker_item` for the edited term.\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make t